snippet.textDisplay: You've literally said exactly what I've said in group discussion about this year's Rewind of what YouTube should have done and included and how. If you and I, complete strangers with very little in common, came up with the exact same solution, why was no one at YouTube able to come up with the same? Perhaps they should ask creators what they want to see? They had PewdiePie review up, but by then it was already done. Ask first, not ask "is this good enough?" once it's complete. Really hope YouTube hasn't completely given up, or would love to see them pass the torch to the creators to do it right. I always looked forward to the Rewinds.

“There is no chance that I would ever be mentioned on a list of top-liked creators on the platform. (We’re not that well-liked)” (4:25-4:32).

Using what metric? What level of “likability” and what audience? I’m genuinely curious, because Theorist Media has 20M+ subscribers between two channels that regularly land on the Trending tab. There are evidently 31 million YouTube channels with ten or more subscribers - looks like The Game Theorists channel is ranked 347th, just above Sam Smith and Gordon Ramsey. On YouTube, The Game Theorists are more popular than JLo (359th). By what standards that matter are Theorist Media’s two channels “not liked”? Thanks.

snippet.textDisplay: Thank you SO much for your point about virtue signalling. So many people SAY the right thing, instead of just DOING the right thing. Goodness speaks for itself. You can be representative and progressive by just doing it, not being preachy. Because, at the end of the day, you don't need to be preachy if you're already doing the right thing. And great points about the state of YouTube. We can't kid ourselves anymore: YouTube is a media machine, it has been for years. Not a creator platform, it's a website where it's back to survival of the wealthiest and most popular, and independent creators are merely allowed to try. But...it's all we got. Let's just hope it can sort itself out.
snippet.textOriginal: Thank you SO much for your point about virtue signalling. So many people SAY the right thing, instead of just DOING the right thing. Goodness speaks for itself.
